MA Chidambaram Stadium

M. A. Chidambaram Stadium, commonly known as the Chepauk Stadium, is a cricket stadium in Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India. Established in 1916, it is the second oldest cricket stadium in the country It is owned and operated by Tamil Nadu Cricket Association. The stadium is located at Chepauk, a few hundred meters from Marina beach along the Bay of Bengal.

EDEN GARDENS,KOLKATA

Eden Gardens is an international cricket stadium in Kolkata, India. Established in 1864, it is the oldest and second-largest cricket stadium in India and third-largest in the world. The stadium currently has a capacity of 68,000.It is owned and operated by Cricket Association of Bengal and is the home ground of the Kolkata Knight Riders.
